      "role": "user",
      "content": "The \"updated data\" angle sounds okay, but they're going to be aggressive. One of the reporters actually has a clip of the candidate saying the Tax Act was \"fundamentally flawed\" just three weeks ago. If we say it's about new data, they're gonna pounce and ask why we didn't have that data three weeks ago. Can we just be straight with them that the political landscape shifted and we're adjusting? Or is that too risky for the consistency numbers?",
